I'm trying to send data to a mysql database with java. To do this I am using  HttpPost to execute a php file to post the information to the database. The problem is nothing is being sent to the php file so nothing to being added to the sql database. 

Here is what I'm currently using:

[code]   	private void useSql(String n, String s) throws ClientProtocolException, IOException {
   		ArrayList<NameValuePair> inp = new ArrayList<NameValuePair>();
   		inp.add(new BasicNameValuePair("name",n));
   		inp.add(new BasicNameValuePair("score",s));
   		HttpClient httpclient = new DefaultHttpClient();
   		HttpPost httppost = new HttpPost("http://amazing-apps.com/post.php");
   		httppost.setEntity(new UrlEncodedFormEntity(inp));
   		httpclient.execute(httppost);
   	}[/code]
